               <physDesc rend="visible">



                  <p>Parchment codex of the 14th century.</p>



                  <objectDesc form="codex">



                     <supportDesc material="chart">



                        <support>Parchment.</support>



                        <extent>342 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">



                              <height>140</height>



                              <width>95</width>



                           </dimensions>
                           <dimensions type="written" unit="mm">



                              <height>90/85</height>



                              <width>55</width>



                           </dimensions>
                        </extent>



                        <foliation>
                           <p>342 folios (+ 3 unfoliated modern paper flyleaves at the beginning and
                              1 older and 3 modern unfoliated paper flyleaves at the end).</p>
                        </foliation>



                        <collation>
                           <p>35 quires: i10 (folios 1-10), ii10 (folios 11-20), iii12 (folios
                              21-32), iv-xvii10 (folios 33-172), xviii8 (folios 173-180), xix8-1
                              (folios 181-187), xx-xxxiv10 (folios 188-337), xxxv8 (folios 338-343),
                              after folio 342 - 2 unfoliated leaves.</p>
                        </collation>



                     </supportDesc>



                     <layoutDesc>



                        <layout columns="1" ruledLines="19" writtenLines="19">
                           <p>Uniform layout.</p>
                           <p>Initial words written in larger characters.</p>
                           <p>Catchwords (decorated) at the end of the quires.</p>
                           <p>Hair side and flesh side are distinguishable. </p>
                           <p>The manuscript is imperfect at the beginning, and there is a gap after
                              folio 152. </p>
                           <p>Erased text (folio 26v). </p>
                           <p>Ruling by hard point (bifolium by bifolium) and pricking (in outer
                              margins only) are visible.</p>
                        </layout>



                     </layoutDesc>



                  </objectDesc>



                  <handDesc hands="1">



                     <summary> Italian square and semi-cursive script, partially punctuated. <name
                           type="person" role="scribe">Mosheh ben Yeḳutiel Ḥefets Tsifroni</name>:
                        inscribed with his name in the colophon, <name type="place">Forli</name>,
                        [5]143 [<date calendar="Gregorian">1383</date>] (folio 323v); probably his
                        arms (folio 259v, 325).</summary>



                     <handNote script="Hebrew" scope="major"/>



                  </handDesc>



                  <additions>
                     <p>12 illustrations were added in 2nd or 3rd quarter of the fifteenth century,
                        produced in Veneto, Italy.</p>
                  </additions>



